# 🏗️ ULTRAPLAN: Complete MAGI Web App Redesign — Zero Bug Tolerance

## Executive Summary

After reading all 18 frontend pages, the full backend server.js, and the Caddy configuration, I've identified a system that is *visually impressive* but *structurally fragile*. The glass-morphism dark theme is genuinely beautiful, and the individual page designs show good taste. However, the architecture is a house of cards: every page is an island, there's no authentication enforcement, no consistent error handling, and mobile UX is hit-or-miss. This plan transforms MAGI from "18 separate HTML files with a shared aesthetic" into "a cohesive application with shared infrastructure and zero-tolerance reliability."

---

## 1. Problem Analysis

### 1.1 UX Issues
| Issue | Severity | Pages Affected |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| No global navigation — trapped in each page, must go back to dashboard | HIGH | All 18 pages |
| No loading states for API calls | HIGH | settings, monitor, analytics, tasks, leads, icat, knowledge |
| No empty states (first-use experience) | MEDIUM | tasks, pipeline, knowledge, vault |
| Inconsistent mobile layouts — some pages untested on mobile | HIGH | leads (sidebar won't collapse), roundtable (sidebar becomes scrollable strip), mission (grid breaks) |
| No back button / breadcrumb on most pages — only MAGI logo link | MEDIUM | Most pages |
| Chat page welcome grid has 3-column layout that breaks at narrow widths | MEDIUM | chat |
| Sidebar toggle state not persisted across page loads | LOW | chat, vault |
| No keyboard shortcuts documented | LOW | vault (has Ctrl+S/N), others none |

### 1.2 DX Issues (Developer Experience)
| Issue | Severity | Impact |
|-------|----------|--------|
| Every page re-implements: CSS reset, CSS variables, font imports, body background orbs, toast system, escape function, timeAgo function, auth check | CRITICAL | ~600 lines duplicated across pages |
| Two different CSS variable sets (dashboard uses `--bg:#0a0e1a`, most pages use `--bg:#060a14`) | HIGH | Visual inconsistency |
| Three different markdown rendering approaches: marked.js in chat/vault, custom regex parser in roundtable, knowledge uses both | HIGH | Different rendering quality per page |
| Auth token not checked on any page except login auto-redirect | CRITICAL | All pages accessible without login |
| Toast implementations differ: some position fixed-top (chat), some fixed-bottom (all others) | LOW | Inconsistency |
| Lucide icons loaded from unpkg CDN on every page — will fail offline | MEDIUM | All pages |

### 1.3 Reliability Issues
| Issue | Severity | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| **No auth enforcement on page load** | CRITICAL | Only login page checks token. Every other page loads without authentication — APIs may fail silently |
| **WebSocket has no heartbeat** | HIGH | Chat page does respond to `ping` from server, but if connection drops silently there's no client-side heartbeat to detect it |
| **WebSocket reconnect is naive** | HIGH | Chat page just does `setTimeout(connectWS, 3000)` — no exponential backoff, no max retries, no user notification of repeated failure |
| **No 401 handling on API calls** | CRITICAL | If token expires, fetch calls return errors but pages don't redirect to login |
| **Memory leaks in monitor page** | HIGH | `setInterval(loadAll, 30000)` never cleared, Lucide icons re-created on every refresh |
| **Memory leaks in notifications** | MEDIUM | Same 30s interval, never cleared |
| **Roundtable stores history in localStorage** | MEDIUM | localStorage has 5-10MB limit; 50 full roundtable conversations could exceed this |
| **XSS in roundtable** | HIGH | Custom markdown renderer doesn't escape HTML: `renderMarkdown()` function is regex-based, no sanitization |
| **No error boundaries** | HIGH | A single JS error in rendering kills the entire page |
| **API URL inconsistency** | MEDIUM | Settings page uses `/api`, `/council-api`, and `/magi2-api` — three different API bases |

